    "body": "<!-- markdownlint-disable -->\n\n## Purpose\n\nWe were unsafely cloning from main for each of these. Now that we have this script called in CI (and the related tests are failing), we should upgrade intentionally.\n\nhttps://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/blob/a9082a4d144e516d0ee00bacfa0dca9609b6b2c3/docker/Dockerfile#L441-L447\n\nMany tests are now failing because they were just gated on these packages being installed, but they should also have gates for the number of GPUs required. Updated this for:\n\n```\ntest_pplx_moe.py\ntest_pplx_cutlass_moe.py\ntest_modular_kernel_combinations.py\ntest_deepep_moe.py\ntest_deepep_deepgemm_moe.py\n```\n\nThanks to @bnellnm for helping figure this out\n\n## Test Plan\n\n## Test Result\n\n## (Optional) Documentation Update\n\n---\n<details>\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\n\n- [ ] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\n- [ ] The test plan, such as providing test command.\n- [ ] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\n</details>\n\n",
